WEBVTT

00:06.592 --> 00:08.677
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:37.683 --> 01:39.726
<i>(PAPA WAS A ROLLING STONE PLAYING)</i>

01:39.851 --> 01:42.813
MADELINE: Oh, my goodness.
Oh! (CHUCKLES)

01:42.896 --> 01:45.023
ED: Ah, good one, Ziggy.
MADELINE: That was...

01:45.107 --> 01:46.942
- Yeah. Work it out.
- ED: Oh, my. Go, go, go!

01:47.025 --> 01:48.568
MADELINE: Work it out, sister.
ED: Yes.

01:48.694 --> 01:50.946
Oh, my gosh. Karate star.

01:52.447 --> 01:53.532
Oh.

02:03.375 --> 02:04.459
<i>(mums)</i>

02:22.936 --> 02:23.979
(INAUDIBLE)

02:42.164 --> 02:43.248
(DOORBELL RINGS)

02:59.097 --> 03:00.182
- What?
-(GUNSHOT ECHOES)

03:07.439 --> 03:10.275
MADELINE: I should have never googled him,
or stirred you up like that.

03:10.359 --> 03:12.986
This is my problem in life,
I can never let dead dogs lie.

03:13.111 --> 03:16.114
Well, but that's the problem, he's not dead.

03:16.782 --> 03:19.242
For all we know,
he's out there right now assaulting women.

03:19.326 --> 03:22.871
Can I ask you,
when you went on this little road trip,

03:22.954 --> 03:24.289
did you take your gun?

03:26.958 --> 03:27.959
No.

03:28.043 --> 03:30.128
- You don't sound sure.
- I didn't take my gun.

03:30.212 --> 03:33.840
And had this Saxon Baker been the guy,
what would you have done?

03:33.965 --> 03:35.884
Were there others?

03:35.967 --> 03:38.512
Other Saxons in your Internet search?

03:39.179 --> 03:42.099
Listen, you moved to Monterey to start over.
To build a future.

03:42.182 --> 03:45.060
I suggest you focus on that. Not the past.

03:45.143 --> 03:46.186
(SCOFFS)

03:53.318 --> 03:55.153
(WIND BLOWING)

03:58.156 --> 03:59.991
PERRY: (WHISPERING) You're gonna kill me.

04:01.576 --> 04:03.829
I have to go to Phoenix tomorrow morning.

04:05.497 --> 04:07.666
I'll be back Thursday night.

04:09.584 --> 04:12.379
But it's the play and it's opening night.

04:13.046 --> 04:14.423
Oh...

04:16.382 --> 04:19.344
Well, well. I'll see it when I get back.

04:21.846 --> 04:24.224
It's opening night.

04:24.349 --> 04:30.105
Madeline's gonna be so disappointed.
It's a whole big thing.

04:30.188 --> 04:32.315
I don't want you going to the premiere either.

04:32.399 --> 04:33.525
What?

04:34.359 --> 04:36.278
Come to Phoenix with me.

04:37.362 --> 04:38.405
Baby, I can't...

04:38.530 --> 04:42.451
Look I know "Come to Phoenix with me" isn't
the most romantic thing you've ever heard,

04:42.534 --> 04:44.536
-but we can...
-(LAUGHING)

04:44.619 --> 04:46.496
We can sneak off to Sedona, for a night...

04:46.580 --> 04:49.124
- No, I can't do that.
- Why?

04:49.207 --> 04:52.502
Because she will never speak to me again.
It's a big thing for her.

04:52.586 --> 04:55.130
- Madeline's beginning to piss me off.
- Oh...

04:57.215 --> 05:01.011
How often do we get a chance to sneak away,
just the two of us?

05:01.094 --> 05:03.555
- Look what you're doing! Look at it...
- What, what?

05:04.473 --> 05:09.060
You're the one who suddenly has to leave,
and I am the one who disappoints... (SCOFFS)

05:10.395 --> 05:12.272
- I'm just trying to be romantic.
-(SIGHS)

05:13.565 --> 05:14.566
Huh?

05:15.150 --> 05:17.027
Just a little romantic here.

05:17.110 --> 05:18.570
- JOSH: Mom!
- Mmm.

05:25.285 --> 05:26.328
<i>NATHAN: I don't want t0...</i>

05:26.411 --> 05:28.580
Divorced people are not
supposed to be friends.

05:28.663 --> 05:31.082
Supposed to be civil or
have dinner together, and...

05:32.459 --> 05:36.004
You know, it's okay for things
to be ugly sometimes.

05:36.087 --> 05:37.964
That's like life.

05:38.089 --> 05:42.344
Got it, life can be ugly.
I'll make a note of that. Thank you.

05:43.470 --> 05:45.722
-(CHUCKLES)
- What are you doing?

05:45.805 --> 05:48.892
Oh, just puttering around
in the garden, honey.

05:48.975 --> 05:51.645
Trying to help things grow and evolve.

05:52.437 --> 05:53.605
(SCOFFS)

05:53.688 --> 05:59.361
Hey, what have you been doing all day
behind your closed door there, locked away?

05:59.444 --> 06:00.570
Working on your secret project?

06:00.654 --> 06:02.906
Yeah, well, it won't be
a secret for much longer.

06:02.989 --> 06:06.159
- My official unveiling is on Wednesday.
- Wow.

06:06.493 --> 06:08.119
You've been working really hard on this.

06:08.203 --> 06:10.413
Well, colleges look for
passion projects now, you know.

06:10.497 --> 06:14.042
It's not just about, like, your GPA,
and being captain of volleyball.

06:14.125 --> 06:15.335
Finally. (CHUCKLING)

06:15.460 --> 06:16.503
Yeah.

06:16.628 --> 06:18.713
(WIND CHIMES TINKLING)

06:19.965 --> 06:23.009
I wanted to say,
thank you for having the dinner on Tuesday.

06:23.635 --> 06:26.680
I know you and Mom really don't get along,
or necessarily want to,

06:27.681 --> 06:31.142
but the idea that we could all be together
sometimes like we used to,

06:32.394 --> 06:33.645
it's kind of cool.

06:42.195 --> 06:44.364
- Good night.
- BONNIE: Good night, sweetie.

06:55.917 --> 06:57.961
Don't. Just cut.

06:58.044 --> 07:00.964
MADELINE: <i>I feel like I just opened up</i>
a <i>giant can of violent worms.</i>

07:01.047 --> 07:02.090
So how did you leave it with her?

07:02.173 --> 07:03.508
<i>Well, I tried to diffuse her.</i>

07:03.592 --> 07:05.468
<i>Imagine me, playing the role of diffuser.</i>

07:05.552 --> 07:07.887
<i>I should just stay out of other people's lives.</i>

07:08.930 --> 07:09.973
I'll talk to her.

07:10.056 --> 07:11.474
<i>What could you possibly say?</i>

07:11.558 --> 07:12.601
Excuse me?

07:12.684 --> 07:14.394
Well, I mean,
she can hardly relate to my life.

07:14.519 --> 07:16.229
What on Earth is she gonna do
to identify with yours?

07:16.354 --> 07:18.356
Which is just a tick north of perfect.

07:18.523 --> 07:21.109
(SIGHS) My life isn't perfect, Madeline.

07:21.192 --> 07:23.361
Bad things have happened to me.

07:23.445 --> 07:25.822
I do understand the concept. (SIGHS)

07:25.905 --> 07:28.158
<i>I'm sorry, I've offended you.
I can hear it in your voice.</i>

07:28.241 --> 07:29.326
<i>Just tell me to go fuck myself.</i>

07:29.409 --> 07:31.953
No, I'm not gonna do that.

07:33.872 --> 07:37.083
- I just don't think she's a dangerous person.
<i>- Really?</i>

07:37.208 --> 07:39.044
<i>I'm starting to get a little bit worried.</i>

07:40.712 --> 07:41.963
I'm gonna have to call you back.

07:42.047 --> 07:43.214
<i>Is Perry there?</i>

07:44.549 --> 07:46.760
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

07:46.885 --> 07:49.054
I'm just gonna have to call you back, all right?

07:49.137 --> 07:50.930
<i>Okay. Good night, honey.</i>

07:51.056 --> 07:52.098
Okay.

07:55.977 --> 07:59.606
Tell me, baby.
What bad things have happened to you?

08:15.580 --> 08:18.249
<i>(PAPA WAS A ROLLING STONE PLAYING
VIA SPEAKER)</i>

08:20.960 --> 08:22.879
All right, put it away, babe. We're pulling up.

08:22.962 --> 08:24.547
Wait, my favorite part.

08:24.631 --> 08:26.800
Ziggy, you can watch it
when you get home from school.

08:26.925 --> 08:28.510
- Put it away.
- Here it is.

08:28.593 --> 08:29.844
(KNOCKING ON WINDOW)

08:31.596 --> 08:32.639
- Hey.
- Hi.

08:32.764 --> 08:34.182
Can you come see me?

08:34.265 --> 08:35.308
Yeah.

08:35.600 --> 08:40.270
There is evidently a petition circulating,

08:40.355 --> 08:43.274
calling for Ziggy's suspension.

08:43.357 --> 08:44.567
His suspension?

08:44.651 --> 08:48.446
I am furious about it, as is Mr. Nippal,
and we will get it stopped.

08:49.864 --> 08:53.368
- But in the meantime...
- Are people actually signing this?

08:53.451 --> 08:55.203
Yeah, it seems so.

08:55.286 --> 08:57.080
He's six!

08:57.163 --> 08:59.040
We don't even know that he's the bully!

08:59.124 --> 09:01.418
I know. I just found out about it myself.

09:01.501 --> 09:05.130
And we will absolutely handle it,
Ziggy will, of course, not be suspended.

09:06.506 --> 09:08.049
<i>HARPER".
I'm not ashamed to say I started the petition.</i>

09:08.133 --> 09:09.551
The school was doing nothing.

09:09.634 --> 09:13.096
That Harper was so far up Renata's ass,
she could have chewed her food for her.

09:13.179 --> 09:14.222
I signed the petition.

09:14.305 --> 09:16.349
- I signed it.
- I accidently signed it.

09:16.474 --> 09:17.892
The school was not doing nothing.

09:17.976 --> 09:19.853
MS. BARNES:
The petition, we will get squashed.

09:19.978 --> 09:20.979
I am more concerned...

09:22.063 --> 09:26.317
Some of the children have been instructed
not to play with Ziggy...

09:26.526 --> 09:28.194
(ELECTRICITY HUMMING)

09:35.660 --> 09:37.579
(KIDS CHATTERING)

09:42.834 --> 09:45.587
- You behind this petition?
- Excuse me?

09:45.670 --> 09:48.214
- I asked you a fucking question.
- Hey, whoa, whoa, calm down.

09:48.339 --> 09:49.340
- Calm down.
- Was it you?

09:49.424 --> 09:51.801
What're you gonna do, huh?
Choke me? (SNICKERS)

09:51.885 --> 09:53.553
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hey!

09:53.678 --> 09:55.930
-'Sc:use me, don't you...
- Stop, stop.

09:56.181 --> 09:58.725
- Oh, my God, my eye!
- What the hell is wrong with you?

09:58.850 --> 10:02.061
If they had any sense they would have
canceled Trivia Night right then and there.

10:02.187 --> 10:05.273
I'd actually planned on skipping Trivia Night
until the eye gouging.

10:06.524 --> 10:08.026
I should have taken that job in Reykjavik.

10:08.109 --> 10:09.444
I'm gonna sue you!

10:09.736 --> 10:12.113
-(GROANS)
-ls her eye okay?

10:12.197 --> 10:13.782
Apparently. (SCOFFS)

10:13.865 --> 10:14.949
She'll be fine.

10:15.033 --> 10:17.410
I need to get out of this town
as soon as possible.

10:17.535 --> 10:18.912
Hold on a second.

10:19.037 --> 10:20.580
Ziggy is very well liked.

10:21.122 --> 10:22.832
Chloe says he's popular.

10:22.916 --> 10:25.126
Even Amabella plays with him.

10:25.210 --> 10:26.294
This is about the parents,

10:26.377 --> 10:29.798
and I'm not gonna have you
bulldozed out of Monterey.

10:29.881 --> 10:31.132
Neither will I, for what it's worth.

10:31.216 --> 10:33.301
Exactly, thank you.

10:33.384 --> 10:36.095
(CHUCKLES) Thank you. Thanks.

10:39.098 --> 10:41.476
A lot of parents are probably
applauding you right now.

10:41.559 --> 10:44.562
There's more than one person
in this town who wants to deck Renata Klein,

10:44.646 --> 10:46.105
yours truly included.

10:46.231 --> 10:48.149
I actually think this is a good thing.

10:48.233 --> 10:50.777
It's high time that people know
they shouldn't fuck with Jane Chapman,

10:51.236 --> 10:53.321
and they're not gonna mess
with your kid, either.

10:53.404 --> 10:55.073
I had my gun.

10:55.156 --> 10:56.449
What?

10:57.242 --> 10:59.994
I had my gun, in my purse
when I went to San Luis Obispo.

11:00.078 --> 11:02.747
I don't think I would have shot him,
but I had it.

11:04.290 --> 11:05.416
Okay.

11:06.918 --> 11:10.880
Well I'm not gonna lie, that gives me pause.

11:10.964 --> 11:13.174
Yeah, it gives me pause, too.

11:14.843 --> 11:16.594
Like I think I'm going insane.

11:18.596 --> 11:23.393
Like I still hope,
that whoever he is, is a nice guy.

11:23.476 --> 11:26.354
That like, maybe that night
was just a bad misunderstanding,

11:26.437 --> 11:28.106
or a night gone wrong,

11:29.482 --> 11:32.277
or he had a bad day,
or his parents got in a car crash.

11:32.360 --> 11:34.112
And like, I make up these crazy excuses

11:34.195 --> 11:38.616
because I'm so desperate to believe
that Ziggy's father is actually a good person.

11:49.544 --> 11:54.841
Well he's been very, um...
(CLICKS TONGUE) Affectionate.

11:54.966 --> 11:57.969
Very cling)'-

11:58.052 --> 12:02.473
Which usually means
he's feeling insecure, or...

12:03.641 --> 12:05.310
Or what?

12:05.393 --> 12:07.645
Or it means I have the power.

12:09.981 --> 12:13.818
Sometimes he has it. Sometimes I have it.
It's like a seesaw.

12:15.695 --> 12:17.739
When do you get the power?

12:18.865 --> 12:20.825
After he hits you?

12:22.827 --> 12:25.747
Yeah, when he hurts me I get the upper hand.

12:28.416 --> 12:32.503
The more he hurts me,
the higher I go, the longer I stay. Until...

12:36.341 --> 12:42.055
He's been, um, ahem,
very loving the last few days.

12:42.180 --> 12:46.017
- But at some point he gets the power back.
- Mmm.

12:49.187 --> 12:52.106
Usually when my bruises fade,

12:54.192 --> 12:56.027
and he doesn't feel as guilty.

12:56.110 --> 12:59.948
He feels insecure,
and then it all happens again.

13:00.031 --> 13:01.324
Where is he now?

13:01.407 --> 13:04.118
He is in Phoenix. He left this morning.

13:09.248 --> 13:11.709
When are you going to leave him, Celeste?

13:12.627 --> 13:15.838
-(SCOFFS)
- When he hurts you badly enough?

13:15.922 --> 13:18.549
When he hurts the children?

13:18.633 --> 13:19.801
He will never hurt the children...

13:19.884 --> 13:22.553
You need to rent an apartment.

13:23.388 --> 13:27.392
Locally, if you don't wanna
disrupt the boys' school.

13:27.475 --> 13:30.728
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
We're getting way ahead of ourselves here.

13:30.812 --> 13:32.480
No, I don't think so.

13:32.563 --> 13:35.066
Stock the refrigerator,

13:35.149 --> 13:38.778
make sure the utilities are paid for,
have the beds set up for the kids.

13:38.903 --> 13:40.989
Get it all ready,

13:42.407 --> 13:45.493
so we can at least remove, "Where on
God's Earth would I go?" from the equation.

13:45.576 --> 13:47.286
You'll have a place,

13:47.745 --> 13:52.166
a mind-set, another life
standing by should you need it,

13:52.250 --> 13:55.169
which we both know you will.

13:55.586 --> 13:59.340
I don't think a therapist should be this, um...

13:59.424 --> 14:01.134
I don't think you should be behaving like this.

14:01.259 --> 14:03.761
I'll get you the number of the
Better Business Bureau, you can report me.

14:03.845 --> 14:07.098
In the meantime,
start documenting the abuse.

14:07.932 --> 14:09.892
Write everything down,

14:09.976 --> 14:13.146
photograph your injuries,
keep doctor reports.

14:13.271 --> 14:15.273
That could be important in a custody battle

14:16.357 --> 14:18.818
and men like your husband
typically do go for custody.

14:18.943 --> 14:23.364
He has the resources,
the money, the contacts,

14:23.448 --> 14:26.534
most importantly,

14:26.617 --> 14:30.538
he has the ego to see this through.

14:30.621 --> 14:33.166
I don't understand why
you're being such an alarmist right now.

14:33.291 --> 14:35.626
- Nothing's...
- Because I'm alarmed.

14:38.337 --> 14:41.299
Have you told anybody else about the abuse?

14:43.468 --> 14:44.469
No.

14:45.470 --> 14:46.929
- Why not?
- I don't know.

14:47.013 --> 14:48.514
If you were to guess...

14:51.976 --> 14:52.977
(SCOFFS)

14:55.354 --> 15:00.485
Perhaps my self-worth is made up
of how other people see me.

15:01.486 --> 15:02.528
(CHUCKLES)

15:03.988 --> 15:05.114
I'm sorry.

15:05.198 --> 15:09.911
I'm just amazed by patients who can harbor
such profound self-awareness

15:09.994 --> 15:12.413
underneath the hard shell of denial.

15:12.497 --> 15:15.166
Find a friend to confide in. Do it today.

15:16.167 --> 15:17.210
(SIGHS) Because...

15:17.335 --> 15:21.506
Because if there is a custody battle,
you know what Perry's lawyer will be asking.

15:21.589 --> 15:25.301
"Did you ever tell anybody, Mrs. Wright?"

15:25.384 --> 15:26.427
Hmm?

15:27.345 --> 15:29.430
"Really, you told nobody at all?

15:29.514 --> 15:31.933
"Is that because it never really happened,

15:32.016 --> 15:34.936
"and you're just making all this up
to win custody?

15:36.562 --> 15:41.901
"In fact, you've repeatedly maintained
what a wonderful husband and father Perry is.

15:42.026 --> 15:43.277
"Haven't you, Mrs. Wright?

15:44.695 --> 15:49.117
"Nobody's ever witnessed this
alleged abuse, ever.

15:49.200 --> 15:50.910
"Isn't that true, Mrs. Wright?

15:52.537 --> 15:53.788
"We only have your word.

15:53.871 --> 15:59.502
"You said he was wonderful,
now you say he's a monster.

15:59.585 --> 16:02.547
"Were you lying then, or are you lying now?"

16:05.091 --> 16:06.717
You're a lawyer.

16:07.885 --> 16:10.972
You know how important it is
to have a witness.

16:14.559 --> 16:15.643
- Hey.
- Hello.

16:15.726 --> 16:18.229
- Juliette? Right?
- RENATA: What do you want?

16:24.569 --> 16:25.611
Uh...

16:28.990 --> 16:32.618
I just wanted to say that I'm so sorry.

16:34.078 --> 16:36.497
I completely lost control,
and I stepped out of line,

16:36.581 --> 16:39.250
and I should've never shoved you like that,
there are no excuses.

16:39.375 --> 16:40.793
And I'm so sorry.

16:41.252 --> 16:43.254
Yeah. (SCOFFS)

16:51.929 --> 16:57.685
The truth is, is I finally realized that I've been
feeling exactly what you must be feeling.

16:57.768 --> 17:01.230
There's nothing worse than your child
being victimized, right?

17:03.774 --> 17:07.737
So, I understand and completely empathize
with what you're going through.

17:09.070 --> 17:12.909
I am as sure as any parent can be
that Ziggy is innocent.

17:12.992 --> 17:14.410
I took him to a child psychologist.

17:14.492 --> 17:17.038
And she examined him and tested him,

17:17.121 --> 17:19.207
and said that he was a gentle young boy

17:19.290 --> 17:22.460
who's completely incapable
of doing what he's been accused of.

17:23.836 --> 17:25.630
Renata, I am at my wit's end.

17:26.422 --> 17:28.841
I don't know what to do anymore.

17:28.966 --> 17:31.260
Does Amabella still say that he's hurting her?

17:32.970 --> 17:37.141
No. She says he's a sweet boy.

17:37.975 --> 17:40.311
And orientation?

17:41.646 --> 17:43.856
Well, she hasn't taken back the accusation.

17:45.107 --> 17:48.486
But she refuses to talk to us
about anything further.

17:50.613 --> 17:53.366
You think you're at your wits' end,

17:53.491 --> 17:57.495
my daughter's the one getting hurt,
and I can't stop it.

17:59.497 --> 18:01.123
(SOFTLY) I'm so sorry.

18:03.125 --> 18:04.335
Me, too.

18:09.548 --> 18:10.883
Thank you.

18:12.343 --> 18:13.678
Thank you.

18:17.306 --> 18:19.600
Yeah. My baby lost another baby tooth.

18:19.684 --> 18:21.811
- I put it under my pillow.
- Good.

18:21.894 --> 18:24.981
There is no Tooth Fairy, idiot.
It's Mom and Dad.

18:25.064 --> 18:26.983
Would you please get me a tissue?

18:27.066 --> 18:29.193
- Is it bleeding?
- No, not a lot.

18:29.735 --> 18:31.487
(GROWLING)

18:31.570 --> 18:33.489
- Are there any bad teenagers in here?
- Dad!

18:33.572 --> 18:35.116
What are you doing here?

18:35.199 --> 18:36.575
Hey, boys.

18:37.535 --> 18:40.204
Don't we have a premiere to attend tonight?

18:41.163 --> 18:42.999
You made it back for the play?

18:43.082 --> 18:44.667
I wouldn't miss it for the world.

18:44.750 --> 18:46.002
They're gonna kiss.

18:46.085 --> 18:47.128
You did that for me?

18:47.211 --> 18:50.006
Yeah, of course.

18:50.089 --> 18:51.424
Thank you.

18:54.760 --> 18:56.929
Wow! Kazowie.

18:57.054 --> 18:58.264
Did you say, "Kazowie"?

18:58.389 --> 19:00.933
I did. You look fantastic.

19:01.058 --> 19:02.184
Thank you, honey.

19:02.268 --> 19:03.352
What, you got a big date or something?

19:03.436 --> 19:05.896
As a matter of fact I do. A very big date.

19:06.063 --> 19:10.192
Oh. Congrats on your opening night!

19:10.276 --> 19:12.611
Thank you, honey.

19:12.737 --> 19:14.947
I don't really have
anything to do with it anymore.

19:15.072 --> 19:16.741
You have a huge amount to do with it.

19:16.866 --> 19:19.910
It wouldn't even be happening, but for you.
Are you kidding?

19:23.247 --> 19:25.082
