37:10.772 --> 37:13.483
Sorry, poor form.
I know you're friends with Madeline.

37:13.608 --> 37:14.651
It's all good.

37:14.734 --> 37:18.738
- Hey!
- Hey! Everything okay here?

37:18.822 --> 37:19.823
RENATA: Everything's great.

37:19.948 --> 37:21.741
JANE: So nice of you to ask, Harper.

37:21.825 --> 37:25.328
You know, schools should set up
special commendations for gestures like that.

37:25.412 --> 37:26.454
Maybe I'll start a petition.

37:27.914 --> 37:29.833
(CHUCKLES) "Petition"! Touché.

37:29.916 --> 37:32.168
All right, I'm going to work, girls.
See you later.

37:32.293 --> 37:33.336
Bye.

37:34.170 --> 37:36.339
We just want our children
to be safe, that's all.

37:36.464 --> 37:38.091
Of course we do. It takes a village.

37:38.174 --> 37:39.592
Got to have each other's backs, right?

37:40.427 --> 37:42.011
Who's got yours?

37:44.764 --> 37:46.182
<i>There was this rumor whipping around</i>

37:46.266 --> 37:49.352
that Jane and Renata
had settled their differences.

37:49.436 --> 37:50.478
I never bought it.

37:50.812 --> 37:54.524
I believe women are
chemically incapable of forgiveness.

38:01.364 --> 38:02.365
It's pretty, huh?

38:05.368 --> 38:08.496
So this is our two-bedroom, two-bath.

38:08.621 --> 38:09.664
Mmm-hmm.

38:09.956 --> 38:12.625
You know, some of the units come furnished,
but personally,

38:12.709 --> 38:15.295
- I think the décor is hideous.
-(CHUCKLES)

38:15.378 --> 38:17.714
And they're on the ground floor,
so you don't get this view.

38:17.797 --> 38:19.382
No, unfurnished is fine.

38:21.050 --> 38:23.887
- It's definitely on the Monterey city limits?
- Yeah.

38:24.012 --> 38:25.638
We're Southwest Monterey.

38:27.348 --> 38:28.975
And it's available now?

38:29.058 --> 38:31.060
You can move in tomorrow.

38:33.688 --> 38:35.398
- What a beautiful sunset.
- Mmm.

38:40.653 --> 38:42.655
Do you think I'd be able to
come back a little later

38:42.739 --> 38:44.407
and spend some time here by myself?

38:44.908 --> 38:46.576
- Yeah.
-It probably sounds weird.

38:46.701 --> 38:47.827
No, it doesn't sound weird.

38:47.911 --> 38:50.079
I mean, it's possibly
where you'll be living, right?

38:50.205 --> 38:52.540
I'm just going to leave you the key,
and I'll clear it with the office,

38:52.624 --> 38:54.834
-and just take as much time as you need.
- That's amazing. Thank you.

38:54.918 --> 38:57.587
Just call me tomorrow. Let me know.

39:03.718 --> 39:05.178
(SIGHS)

39:20.276 --> 39:22.111
ED: If you feel yourself getting angry,

39:22.195 --> 39:25.198
just remember it's all about
getting along for Abigail's sake.

39:25.281 --> 39:28.409
I'm going to be fine. I took a little something.

39:29.911 --> 39:31.412
Just a half.

39:33.289 --> 39:35.416
This is a good thing that we're doing.

39:41.631 --> 39:44.133
MADELINE: Such a long drive...

39:44.217 --> 39:45.426
ED: Good. Everything looks good.

39:48.429 --> 39:50.306
And the chef, not too bad.

39:50.431 --> 39:51.808
The cook's even better.

39:53.768 --> 39:55.061
Uh, Madeline, do you want some more bread?

39:55.144 --> 39:57.730
- Mmm, yes, please. So yummy.
- Honey, will you pass that? Thank you.

39:57.814 --> 40:00.483
Bonnie, I love this music. Is this Adele?

40:00.567 --> 40:02.443
Uh, no, it's Sade, actually.

40:02.819 --> 40:03.987
We should get this, honey.

40:04.070 --> 40:05.321
Oh, we have it.

40:05.405 --> 40:06.489
BONNIE: Red wine, anyone?

40:06.573 --> 40:07.907
I know white goes with fish, but I like red.

40:07.991 --> 40:09.075
MADELINE: Yes, please.

40:11.327 --> 40:12.412
(LAUGHS)

40:12.620 --> 40:13.997
Down the hatch.

40:14.080 --> 40:15.748
I love this place setting,

40:15.832 --> 40:17.917
like when there's extra forks
and extra spoons,

40:18.001 --> 40:19.419
especially the little tiny forks.

40:19.502 --> 40:20.837
-(CHUCKLES)
-it feels so special, doesn't it?

40:20.962 --> 40:22.672
I just want to use all of them.

40:22.797 --> 40:24.674
The little ones are for the oysters.

40:24.757 --> 40:27.677
And I love these really creative little cups.

40:27.760 --> 40:29.262
- They're clay. I think they're from Mexico.
- Yeah.

40:29.345 --> 40:30.346
MADELINE: That's so nice.

40:30.471 --> 40:36.185
Ed prefers more traditional
glass cups for wine, but these are...

40:36.269 --> 40:38.104
I'm actually more kind of a beer guy, but...

40:38.187 --> 40:39.188
Oh, do you want some beer?

40:39.314 --> 40:40.356
- Oh, no, no, no.
- We have some.

40:40.481 --> 40:41.524
- Are you sure?
- Sit down.

40:41.649 --> 40:43.610
- You've done enough.
- And since we're talking about wineglasses,

40:43.693 --> 40:44.944
-let's have a toast!
- A toast.

40:45.028 --> 40:46.195
- Yes, toast.
- Toast.

40:46.988 --> 40:48.031
The, uh...

40:48.656 --> 40:49.949
To, um... For...

40:50.033 --> 40:53.202
- I should make a toast.
- BONNIE: Please.

40:53.328 --> 40:56.372
To Nathan and Bonnie.

40:56.497 --> 40:58.625
- Because I heard...
- And none of us killing each other.

40:58.708 --> 41:00.335
(LAUGHS) Yeah, right.

41:00.710 --> 41:02.879
-(LAUGHTER)
- I'm just kidding.

41:06.007 --> 41:07.634
This is yummy wine.

41:07.717 --> 41:09.719
- BONNIE: Mmm, is it?
-It's really good.

41:11.012 --> 41:12.972
Uh, is Abigail going to join us for dinner?

41:13.056 --> 41:14.807
She'll be down for dessert.

41:14.891 --> 41:17.560
She says she can only be stuck
with the grown-ups for so long.

41:17.644 --> 41:18.728
Yeah.

41:19.228 --> 41:21.397
I think she's just wanting us
to have some bonding time.

41:21.522 --> 41:24.567
Teenagers. Oh, she's probably working
on her secret project.

41:24.692 --> 41:25.902
Mmm.

41:26.027 --> 41:27.737
MADELINE: I'm so curious.

41:27.820 --> 41:30.073
- Do you guys know what that is?
- Mmm-hmm.

41:30.156 --> 41:31.866
Yeah, we just found out, what it is. Yeah.

41:32.533 --> 41:34.744
- No way.
- Do tell.

41:36.412 --> 41:38.081
Baby? (CLEARS THROAT)

41:38.331 --> 41:41.042
It's unconventional. It's even a little radical.

41:41.668 --> 41:42.919
Good.

41:43.044 --> 41:45.421
Listen, when I first heard about it,
I overreacted,

41:45.505 --> 41:49.258
and I just got to caution you guys
to take a breath, process it,

41:49.342 --> 41:51.260
before jumping to a judgment.

41:51.344 --> 41:53.262
MADELINE:
Okay, can you just tell us what it is?

41:53.388 --> 41:54.597
(CLEARS THROAT)

41:55.223 --> 41:56.349
us... (LAUGHS)

41:56.432 --> 41:58.768
Well, she's attempting to raise money
for Amnesty International.

41:58.893 --> 42:00.603
- All right.
- So she showed me her website.

42:00.728 --> 42:02.772
- It's like very professionally done.
- Website...

42:07.568 --> 42:08.611
L.-

42:08.736 --> 42:13.616
Abigail is auctioning off her virginity

42:13.741 --> 42:16.452
in order to raise money
to protest sex slavery.

42:17.370 --> 42:19.038
- What?
- Yes.

42:19.122 --> 42:20.248
(SCOFFS)

42:20.415 --> 42:21.791
- Very funny.
- No, I'm being serious.

42:22.750 --> 42:25.044
She said if a seven-year-old
can be sold into sex slavery,

42:25.128 --> 42:26.713
then no one would bat an eye

42:26.796 --> 42:29.966
if a white, rich American girl
would sell hers online.

42:31.300 --> 42:32.719
This is for real?

42:32.802 --> 42:34.470
Look, it's not gone live yet,

42:34.554 --> 42:36.639
and we have no intention
of letting that happen, obviously.

42:36.723 --> 42:39.726
You know, Nathan,
if this is some sort ofjoke...

42:39.809 --> 42:41.728
This is not funny, Nathan.

42:41.811 --> 42:47.316
Okay, it's shocking, and a bit disturbing,

42:47.442 --> 42:51.821
but I think it is important that we separate
the nobility of the cause

42:51.946 --> 42:54.323
from the misguided means
of pursuing it, you know?

42:55.283 --> 42:57.994
We champion the former
and dissuade her from the latter, right?

42:58.244 --> 42:59.996
-(RETCHES)
- ED: Oh, honey!

43:00.121 --> 43:02.248
- Are you okay?
- That's okay. That's okay. That's okay.

43:02.331 --> 43:03.499
I got it. I got it.

43:03.624 --> 43:06.169
That's a human reaction. That's completely...
Baby, get a...

43:06.294 --> 43:07.336
You okay, honey?

43:07.462 --> 43:09.005
No, I'm not.

43:09.130 --> 43:11.257
- Oh, my God.
- ED: Oh, honey.

43:11.340 --> 43:13.426
Okay. Thank you. Thank you.

43:13.509 --> 43:14.844
That's all right. Here.

43:14.969 --> 43:16.179
That's all right.

43:16.304 --> 43:18.014
This is how you parent, Nathan?

43:18.097 --> 43:21.100
She's been under your roof for two minutes
and now she's some sort of prostitute?

43:21.184 --> 43:22.185
Did <i>I</i> tell you?

43:22.310 --> 43:24.687
- Great parenting!
- All right, let's all just settle for a minute.

43:24.771 --> 43:26.481
Okay? Please. Let's just settle.

43:27.607 --> 43:32.028
Let's remember that we are living in the time
of Facebook, and reality...

43:32.111 --> 43:33.362
Ugh... God damn it!

43:33.696 --> 43:35.615
- Oh, my...
- Shit.

43:35.698 --> 43:37.200
It's the shrimp.

43:37.283 --> 43:39.535
I'd heard that Abigail was a little slutty.

43:39.660 --> 43:41.871
Knowing the mother, I wouldn't be surprised.

43:42.038 --> 43:43.790
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

43:48.044 --> 43:49.837
'BYe,guys.
- Bye.

43:49.921 --> 43:50.963
Where are you going?

43:51.047 --> 43:52.882
Out for dinner with Jane.

43:53.257 --> 43:54.300
(SIGHS)

44:09.732 --> 44:11.067
That's enough.

44:12.485 --> 44:13.694
Abigail!

44:21.035 --> 44:22.286
You're done with dinner already?

44:22.370 --> 44:24.413
Look, I don't even know
where to begin about this,

44:24.497 --> 44:26.165
so I'm just going to go straight to the end.

44:26.249 --> 44:29.752
This is wrong, Abigail. Completely wrong.

44:30.211 --> 44:32.630
And I salute your cause. I really do.

44:32.713 --> 44:33.798
But what?

44:33.881 --> 44:36.300
Saluting a cause?
Recognizing a problem isn't enough.

44:36.384 --> 44:37.718
A person has to do something.

44:37.802 --> 44:40.221
Well, this something is not that, honey.

44:40.304 --> 44:41.430
What about your play?

44:41.514 --> 44:42.723
What about my play?

44:42.807 --> 44:45.226
You said it spoke to you
because it was about finding a purpose in life,

44:45.309 --> 44:46.352
which I get.

44:46.435 --> 44:48.437
Making your mark. I get that.

44:48.521 --> 44:51.315
You're the one who always said
a person's life needs to matter.

44:51.399 --> 44:52.984
- Okay.
- Was it all just bullshit?

44:53.067 --> 44:54.402
No, it's not.

44:54.485 --> 44:56.821
And I'm not going to give you
some long song-and-dance

44:56.904 --> 44:59.574
about how precious and sacred
your beautiful body is.

44:59.657 --> 45:03.327
- Mmm-hmm.
- But it is not for sale, Abigail. Not ever.

45:03.411 --> 45:06.330
No matter what cause, no matter what cost.

45:06.414 --> 45:08.249
And one day,
you're going to look back at this,

45:08.332 --> 45:10.001
probably pretty soon, and think,

45:10.084 --> 45:11.627
"What the fuck was I thinking?

45:11.711 --> 45:14.088
"Why was I going to fuck up my life like that?"

45:14.297 --> 45:16.757
(SCOFFS) Must be nice to be so right.

45:16.841 --> 45:19.010
- I'm not right!
- And so perfect.

45:19.093 --> 45:21.053
I'm not fucking perfect!

45:22.263 --> 45:25.141
You think you know me so well?
I fuck up, too!

45:26.058 --> 45:29.437
I make mistakes.
I've made mistakes bigger than this.

45:30.897 --> 45:31.939
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

45:35.776 --> 45:38.029
Last year I cheated on Ed.

45:40.114 --> 45:41.449
I ended it very quickly.

45:47.455 --> 45:52.835
And the two things I value most in this life
are my kids and my marriage,

45:52.919 --> 45:55.671
and I risked destroying both of them.

45:57.465 --> 46:02.136
Just because I was selfish, or...

46:03.804 --> 46:07.683
So tell me...
Don't tell me I'm perfect, okay?

46:09.101 --> 46:11.062
I know about fucking up.

46:13.648 --> 46:16.817
And fucking up doesn't make
your dad and I get back together.

46:18.736 --> 46:23.783
Fucking up doesn't fix your life, okay?

46:25.701 --> 46:29.580
At least what you were going to do
was for a good cause, and...

46:32.041 --> 46:34.251
I was just being selfish.

46:36.504 --> 46:37.880
Do you still love Ed?

47:00.987 --> 47:02.655
(TV PLAYING)

47:28.222 --> 47:30.725
Mom, watch this.

47:30.808 --> 47:33.185
<i>(PAPA WAS A ROLLING STONE PLAYING)</i>

47:37.106 --> 47:38.649
<i>(SINGING)
September</i>

47:40.067 --> 47:43.946
<i>The day I will always remember, yes I will</i>

47:45.531 --> 47:50.578
<i>Because that was the day
that my daddy died</i>

47:52.955 --> 47:55.875
<i>I never got a chance to see</i>

47:57.043 --> 48:01.088
<i>Never heard nothin'
but bad things about him</i>

48:01.172 --> 48:05.885
<i>Momma I'm depending on you
to tell me the truth</i>

48:09.430 --> 48:11.724
(MUSIC CONTINUES)
